Hundreds of Breidbach residents have blocked the N2 near King William&#8217;s Town in protest over service delivery grievances including the provision of houses. Acting BCM mayor Helen Neale-May has requested the residents to call off the protest however the crowd shouted &#8220;No&#8221;. The residents shouted &#8220;We want houses&#8221;.As part of their grievances, they also want Eastern Cape Premier Phumulo Masualle and President Jacob Zuma to address them.Due to the protest, the N2 near the Berlin turn-off has been closed off.